body:
Port of asynchronous generators and async comprehensions. Probably needs more testing but at least seems to pass the original CPython tests so far.
https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0525/
https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0530/

I'm aware that this is too long for any serious change-by-change review, but the combined patch isn't all that long. At least the scoping changes for comprehensions would be worth a second pair of eyes. They previously didn't support closures, but async comprehensions need to remember their state.

Further changes:
- support for pre-Py3.5.2 async iterators was removed (CPython 3.7 is still in a deprecation phase here)
- exception type checks were optimised in order to speed up (Async)StopIteration handling
- loop variables in scoped (Py3) comprehensions can now be stored in closure objects
- excessive inlining was reduced in some places

Things that don't work:
- async generator finalisation requires Py3.6+, which makes asyncgens quite uninteresting in earlier Python versions as they cannot do any async cleanup (see PEP 525)

commit.message: clean copy of the current AsyncGen implementation proposed for CPython 3.6 to make local changes visible
adapt and escape all copied AsyncGen code for Cython
disable finalisers in CPython < 3.6
allow "args" tuple argument to be NULL in __Pyx__Coroutine_Throw() and only create a tuple if necessary
use more descriptive C label names for yield/yield-from/await
fix AsyncGen type initialisation and instantiation
implement shortcuts for async generators in async-for loop
allow yield in async def functions (which turns them into async generators)
improve generated C code comment
streamline yield object unwrapping in async-gen
prevent passing NULL into async-gen on normal iteration
update PEP 525 implementation to match the code in Py3.6/7 (currently non-functional)
continue to disallow "yield from" in async functions
refactor "yield from" and "await" nodes a little to provide a cleaner split between them (await nodes are not yield-from nodes)
solve most of the issues with failing async-gen tests, some asyncio tests are still failing
add "--failfast" (stop on first failure) mode to test runner (if supported by Python's unittest module)
make internal marker types awaitable in older Python versions
make async generator type async-iterable in older Python versions
unittest fixes and work-arounds for older Python versions
test runner output fixes
unittest fixes and work-arounds for older Python versions
fix test runner option
temporary hack to make test work until we get async comprehensions
add missing preprocessor guard around coroutine dependant code in generic generator utility function
generalise error message that disallows 'yield'/'await'/etc. inside of parallel sections
remove accidental left-over
fix C compiler warnings about unused C function arguments
remove accidentally duplicated finaliser code from the coroutine deallocator function as it must get executed earlier than that
exclude comment from generated C modules
allow yielding exception instances from async generators (previously interpreted them as actual exceptions)
in generators/coroutines, save away the current exception in the 'return' case of finally clauses as 'return' actually raises an (Async)StopIteration exception
tighten test assertions to assure that the exception control flow in await is correct
repair coroutine delegation in await expressions (must pass through "gen->yieldfrom" check)
mark an exceptional case as unlikely()
special case delegation to normal Python generators to avoid Python call indirections
fix crash during shutdown when finaliser is already called
fix C compiler error: missing declarations if generators but not coroutines are used
print full Python version into travis logs (latest dev version seems outdated)
indent comment

Disable asyncio coroutine tests in Py3.4 as coroutines are not iterables but Task() features this beautiful line of code:
        self._coro = iter(coro)  # Use the iterator just in case.
add branch hint
speed up type checks, especially for exceptions (which are used a lot in yield/await)
clarify parentheses to fix C compiler warning
repair "except" on tuples
move less common "except (tuple)" case out of the fast path
fix argument types in call to PyObject_IsSubclass()
fix argument types in call to PyErr_WriteUnraisable()
reduce amount of casts in helper code
do not call PyObject_IsSubclass() with an exception set (instead rely on it being cleared when printing it before)
suppress C compiler warning
restrict an optimisation to Py3 that is not 100% semantically correct in Py2
optimise call to asyncio "firstiter" method for async generators
request inlining of call to trivial function
fix refcounting and error handling bugs in last commit
disable asyncgen tests in Py<3.6 that require the newly added finalisation support
disable another asyncgen test in Py<3.6 that requires the newly added finalisation support
improve error message to hint at potential dependency on Py3.6+ finalisation as most likely cause
implement PEP 530 by allowing async generator expressions
integrate new Py3.6+ couroutine tests and repair misbehaviour in error cases and when async-iterating over awaitable tuple/StopIteration subtypes (however rare that is)
delete outdated syntax tests
repair test assertion after changing exception text
repair scoped comprehensions inside of generators and async functions by allowing their loop variables to be added to closures when necessary
add error case found by CPython test "test_await_15" in test_coroutines_pep492
move protocol error to the right spot to stop overwriting similar exceptions that are already created in __Pyx__Coroutine_GetAwaitableIter()
minor code cleanups
fix DECREF(NULL) for empty comprehensions
adapt finalisation code to what CPython 3.6/7 does, fix error display if not-awaited warning turns into an error
also call coroutine finalisation for non-started instances as we need to warn about them
make syntax tests actually use Cython (and not Python)
fix tests in Py2
discard unused struct in Py2
fix C compiler warning about uninitialised variable
fix some tests in Py3.2
remove support for the pre-Py3.5.2 aiter protocol that slows down the overall implementation
strip comment from generated output
reduce inlining overhead
also special Python coroutines in cygen.send() delegation
fix C compiler warning about unused parameter
fix test
disambiguate attribute name ("is_async_gen" it too close to an existing "is_asyncgen")
fix comment
use potentially faster thread-state access

title: PEP 525: asynchronous generators
